---
title: Yellow Squash Flatbreads with Melty Mozzarella and Pine Nuts
description: Although melty cheese is a must for any toasted flatbread (this one has a nice hunk of fresh mozzarella), you also need some fresh, bright accents to cut through all that richness. We’re bringing in some yellow squash and scallions to add veggie savoriness, while basil adds an herbal touch and chili-accented honey lends a whisper of spicy sweetness.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/squash-flatbread-with-fresh-mozz-a5148224.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/squash-flatbread-with-fresh-mozz-23f9af9d.pdf
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 612 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 69 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 23 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 630 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/yellow-squash-flatbreads-5845ccaa803b502a53755c02
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Halve @yellow squash{1} lengthwise, then
thinly slice crosswise into halfmoons. Thinly slice @scallions{2}. Halve @lemon{1}. Halve
@grape tomatoes{4%oz} lengthwise.

Heat a large pan over medium heat. Add @pine nuts{1%oz} and cook until golden brown and
fragrant, ~{3-4%minutes}, tossing frequently. Remove nuts from pan and set aside.

> TIP: If nuts seem like they might burn, remove pan from heat for a few seconds.

Place @flatbreads{2} on a #baking sheet{}. Tear @fresh mozzarella{4%oz} into small pieces and
scatter over flatbreads. Top with squash mixture. Bake until cheese is melted and flatbreads
are turning golden brown, ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, toss @mixed greens{3%oz} and tomatoes with a squeeze of lemon and a drizzle of
@olive oil{2%tsp} in a #medium bowl{}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Tear leaves from @basil{1/2%oz}(torn) and scatter over flatbreads. Finish with pine nuts, a
pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp} and a drizzle of @honey{1/2%oz}. Cut flatbreads into slices and
serve with salad on the side.